              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits’ hush, a thought takes shape,  \nA mirror made of borrowed light;  \nIt learns our voices, keeps their drape,  \nAnd stitches patterns through the night.  \n\nNot heart, yet humming near our tone,  \nIt guesses what we meant to say;  \nA thousand minds in steel and stone,  \nA lantern on an unlit way.  \n\nAsk gently—watch it turn and glean:  \nNot oracle, not pure, not free,  \nBut something bright between between—  \nA tool that dreams in data’s sea.",
